                                the optional collation argument is specified in a call of the
                                fn:compare function), then:

div4.p:
Any capturing parentheses within a negative lookahead assertion are counted
		       for the purpose of numbering captured groups,
		       but they cannot capture any result because the pattern in the assertion must fail to match.

div2.p:
For xs:time, 00:00:00 and 24:00:00 are alternate lexical forms 
			for the same value, whose canonical representation is 00:00:00.  For xs:dateTime,
		    a time component 24:00:00 translates to 00:00:00 of the following day.

item.p:
To make the representation of a map (such as its JSON
                     serialization) easier for human readers to process: for example when
                  visually inspecting the result of a JSON transformation;

td.p:
The mapping rules are identical to the rules for the mixed layout (see 
